From 6edbaeb0fd3fe0629ec9724236c680f158d893b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pavankumar Nandeshwar <pnandesh@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Jun 2025 12:59:02 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 09/21] UPSTREAM: DP: Use RX HW datastructures in rx path

Use the RX HW datastructures in rx path in place of
existing rxcb structure of skb for storing the rx data.
As, we will be reading most of the rx data directly from
the hw descriptor which was saved in rxcb, we will avoid
excess reads from tlvs, which has impact on performance.

Patch-dependency : None

Signed-off-by: Pavankumar Nandeshwar <pnandesh@qti.qualcomm.com>
